{
  "texts": [
    "• Static heterogeneous GNN methods (HetGNN and HAN) are good at analyzing graph structural information and edge interactions among different types of nodes.",
    "These methods outperform linear regression methods and timesequence models.",
    "However, they are not designed to handle temporal data, a crucial aspect of popularity trend prediction.",
    "• Temporal heterogeneous GNN methods (HGT and Cou-pledGNN) receive inputs similar to the proposed method.",
    "Their performance depends on their underlying architectures and ability to effectively capture temporal and graph structure information."
  ]
}